\begin_layout Standard
As indicated above,
 the functional specification mainly revolves around two main categories:
 the use of the universal remote and the OLED display.
 All of the other technical details are hardware-specific (system architecture),
 or abstracted away from the user.
 You may notice in the diagrams that some functional/system specifications have been removed when compared against the proposal's specifications.
 This mostly stems from complications with dealing with a non-RDS compliant radio module,
 and we had to sacrifice some features (namely volume configuration,
 mute and unmute,
 and callsign multi-tap).
 We also added some features,
 most notably OLED view scrolling.
\end_layout

